The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Friday, May 07, 2004 				 Leader held for playing lout
																								Behrampore, May 6: A Congress panchayat deputy chief was arrested today following allegations of molesting a housewife while campaigning at a village near here last night.																								Police said Ashit Baran Das, who was canvassing for the partys Behrampore candidate Adhir Chowdhury, entered Sukumar Hazras house at Shaktipur village, about 170 km from Calcutta, to seek support and allegedly made advances towards his wife. She had opened the door to him around 10 pm as Hazra was asleep. 																								Das was arrested on the basis of a particular complaint, superintendent of police Gyanwant Singh said. The Congress alleged that it was politically motivated. The arrest is meant to break our partys morale, said Humayun Kabir, a district leader.
